cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the combination of Markov random fields (MRFs) with deep learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given that the paper focuses on the joint learning of deep features and MRF parameters for predicting words from images and multi-class classification of photographs, it is most likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
